Meet <b>MusicMan</b>, our citizen of the week!<br><br>This interesting character lives at <a href='/home/?user=jlake'>4173 Broadway Boulevard</a> in Lakeview, and has lived in Millsberry since August 15, 2004. When he's not playing air guitar to his favorite classic rock albums, you're likely to find him hanging out at school, where he's an outstanding student.<br><br>MusicMan makes quite an impression on everyone he meets. He's got a great jumpshot that helps him excel at basketball, but he's also a bit of a bookworm who is passionate about music. With this combo of physical and intellectual strength, he's a memorable guy on campus and around town.<br><br>His latest fascination has been with the newest technologies, and he has saved up his Millsbucks in order to buy laptops and TVs for his home. The laptops come in handy because he is an avid writer, and sometimes even takes his computer to the lake with him, as the scenery often inspires his poetic side.  <br><br>MusicMan keeps his home minimally decorated, leaving plenty of room for hanging out, and plenty of open wall space for future posters and art canvases he might bring home. His various pets like to curl up on his Sylvie sofas and chase butterflies in the yard.<br><br>So if you see a stylish, confident guy around town in an indigo varsity jacket, say hi and strike up a conversation. With his wide range of interests and hobbies, you could talk about anything from hologram projectors to math theories to jazz piano.<br><br>Thanks for being a good citizen, MusicMan, and congratulations on being named Millberry's citizen of the week!<br></div>
